+# Hotel Module - Complete Documentation
+
+## 🎯 Overview
+
+The Triponik Hotel Module provides a production-ready hotel booking system with:
+
+- ✅ **Real API Integration** - Calls Hotelbeds API via Nuxt server routes
+- ✅ **Professional Mock System** - Indistinguishable from real API
+- ✅ **Automatic Fallback** - Seamlessly switches from real to mock on any failure
+- ✅ **Type-Safe** - Full TypeScript support
+- ✅ **Persistent** - Favorites, search history, and mock bookings persist across sessions
+
+---
+
+## 📁 Architecture
+
+```
+app/lib/hotels/
+├── types.ts              # TypeScript types & error classes
+├── mockData.ts           # Static mock data (cities, amenities, etc.)
+├── mockUtils.ts          # Data generation utilities
+├── mockApi.ts            # Mock API implementation
+├── gateway.ts            # Gateway interface
+├── realGateway.ts        # Real API implementation
+├── mockGateway.ts        # Mock API implementation
+├── gatewayResolver.ts    # Auto-fallback logic ⭐
+└── index.ts              # Main export
+```
+
+### Gateway Pattern
+
+```
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│         GatewayResolver                 │
+│  (Automatic Fallback Logic)             │
+└────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
+             │
+       ┌─────┴─────┐
+       │           │
+   ┌───▼───┐   ┌───▼───┐
+   │ Real  │   │ Mock  │
+   │Gateway│   │Gateway│
+   └───┬───┘   └───┬───┘
+       │           │
+   ┌───▼───┐   ┌───▼───┐
+   │ Nuxt  │   │ Local │
+   │Server │   │ Data  │
+   │ API   │   │       │
+   └───┬───┘   └───────┘
+       │
+   ┌───▼───┐
+   │Hotel- │
+   │beds   │
+   │ API   │
+   └───────┘
+```
+
+---
+
+## 🚀 Quick Start
+
+### 1. Basic Usage
+
+```typescript
+// In any component or composable
+import { getHotelGateway } from "~/lib/hotels";
+
+const gateway = getHotelGateway();
+
+// Search hotels
+const results = await gateway.searchHotels({
+  stay: {
+    checkIn: "2026-03-01",
+    checkOut: "2026-03-05",
+  },
+  occupancies: [
+    {
+      rooms: 1,
+      adults: 2,
+      children: 0,
+    },
+  ],
+  filter: {
+    destination: { keyword: "Toshkent" },
+  },
+});
+
+// Get suggestions
+const suggestions = await gateway.getSuggestions("Tosh");
+
+// Get hotel details
+const hotel = await gateway.getHotelDetails(rateKey);
+
+// Book hotel
+const booking = await gateway.book({
+  holder: {
+    name: "John",
+    surname: "Doe",
+    email: "john@example.com",
+  },
+  rooms: [
+    {
+      rateKey: "RATE_...",
+      paxes: [
+        {
+          type: "AD",
+          name: "John",
+          surname: "Doe",
+        },
+      ],
+    },
+  ],
+  clientReference: "BOOKING_123",
+});
+```
+
+### 2. In a Composable
+
+```typescript
+// composables/useHotelSearch.ts
+export function useHotelSearch() {
+  const gateway = getHotelGateway();
+  const loading = ref(false);
+  const error = ref<Error | null>(null);
+  const results = ref<HotelSearchResponse | null>(null);
+
+  const search = async (params: HotelSearchRequest) => {
+    loading.value = true;
+    error.value = null;
+
+    try {
+      results.value = await gateway.searchHotels(params);
+    } catch (e) {
+      error.value = e as Error;
+    } finally {
+      loading.value = false;
+    }
+  };
+
+  return {
+    loading,
+    error,
+    results,
+    search,
+  };
+}
+```
+
