+## ⚙️ Configuration
+
+### Environment Variables
+
+Create a `.env` file in the project root:
+
+```bash
+# Force mock mode (for UI development without API)
+FORCE_MOCK=false
+
+# Force real mode (fail if API unavailable)
+FORCE_REAL=false
+
+# Nuxt server API base URL (for real mode)
+NUXT_PUBLIC_HOTEL_API_BASE_URL=https://api.triponik.uz
+
+# Server-side credentials (already configured in nuxt.config.ts)
+HOTEL_API_USERNAME=diyorbek
+HOTEL_API_PASSWORD=Mulan2025...
+```
+
+### Runtime Config
+
+The `nuxt.config.ts` already has the configuration:
+
+```typescript
+runtimeConfig: {
+  // Server-side only (private)
+  hotelApiBaseUrl: process.env.HOTEL_API_BASE_URL || 'https://api.triponik.uz',
+  hotelApiUsername: process.env.HOTEL_API_USERNAME || 'diyorbek',
+  hotelApiPassword: process.env.HOTEL_API_PASSWORD || 'Mulan2025...',
+
+  public: {
+    // Client-side accessible (public)
+    baseUrl: process.env.BASE_URL || 'https://api.triponik.uz',
+    apiBaseUrl: '/api', // Nuxt server API
+  }
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## 🎮 Modes
+
+### 1. Auto Mode (Default - Recommended)
+
+Real API with automatic fallback to mock on any failure.
+
+```bash
+# No env vars needed
+npm run dev
+```
+
+**Behavior:**
+
+- Tries real API first
+- If real fails (network, 4xx, 5xx, CORS, timeout) → switches to mock
+- After 3 consecutive failures → permanently switches to mock for session
+- User never knows the difference
+
+### 2. Mock Mode (UI Development)
+
+Always use mock data. Perfect for UI development without API access.
+
+```bash
+FORCE_MOCK=true npm run dev
+```
+
+**Behavior:**
+
+- Never calls real API
+- Uses professional mock data
+- Deterministic results (same search = same hotels)
+- Persists favorites and bookings to localStorage
+
+### 3. Real Mode (Production Testing)
+
+Always use real API. Fails if API is unavailable.
+
+```bash
+FORCE_REAL=true npm run dev
+```
+
+**Behavior:**
+
+- Never uses mock
+- Throws errors if API fails
+- Use this to test real API integration
+
+---
+
+## 📊 Mock Data Features
+
+### Realistic Data Generation
+
+The mock system generates realistic hotel data:
+
+- **12 Uzbekistan cities** (Toshkent, Samarqand, Buxoro, etc.)
+- **15-30 hotels per search** (configurable)
+- **3-5 star ratings** (weighted: 40% 4-star, 30% each for 3 and 5)
+- **1-3 rooms per hotel** (Standard, Deluxe, Suite, Family)
+- **1-3 rates per room** (different board types and payment options)
+- **Realistic pricing** ($50-$400 base, adjusted by board type, payment, refundability)
+- **8-18 amenities** (based on star rating)
+- **Review scores** (8.5-10 for 5-star, 7.5-9 for 4-star, 6.5-8 for 3-star)
+- **Gallery images** (5-8 images from Unsplash)
+- **Nearby attractions** (city-specific)
+
+### Deterministic Results
+
+Mock data uses a seed based on search parameters, so:
+
+- Same destination + dates + guests = same hotels
+- Results persist across page refreshes
+- Consistent for testing and demos
+
+### Persistence
+
+Mock mode persists to `localStorage`:
+
+- Search history
+- Favorites list
+- Mock bookings
+- Generated hotel data
+
